The paper discusses a framework for interactive user interfaces that continuously evolve based on user interactions. This involves collecting and utilizing user feedback in an online setting, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework also includes online learning operators for tasks such as personalization ranking and candidate selection, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents results demonstrating the efficiencies of the framework, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
